Based on information provided by Germany in the context of the international exchange of information under Council Regulation (EC) No 1798/2003, the IA called on taxpayers in March 2007 to file a retrospective tax return, which the taxpayer did not do.
The audit found that the FA carried out further audit work in 2007 in this tax case. It found that the car in question had been sold by the taxpayer to a used car dealer in the Czech Republic.
