4.3 Review of selected cases of risky intra-Community transactions
4.3.1 Findings in the Czech Republic
EUROCANET can be a significant source of information to identify high-risk taxpayers in the Member State of purchase.
In the Czech Republic, the early warning information obtained from EUROCANET is checked by the competent FA with the purchasers.
Since the first quarter of 2008, CZ has included information on sales and taxable suppliers that are considered risky in the EUROCANET system.
Nine Czech taxpayers were selected for the audit,
which had been entered into the EUROCANET by the tax administrations of other Member States, either as suppliers or as transferees.
