4.5.4 Comparison and evaluation
As a result, it should be noted that in the CZ large amounts of information are processed automatically. Among other things, data from VAT audits, as well as key figures from balance sheets, profit and loss statements, are processed in the system.
The CZ is able to steer the selection of risky cases on the basis of a wide range of information.
The same applies to the evaluation and management of VAT checks in general.
The CZ is planning to set up a special tax office for large enterprises in 2012.
In Germany, the tax authorities do not collect comparable amounts of data.
Accordingly, it is more difficult to accomplish these tasks in the same way.
The emphasis is more on the selection of relevant individual cases.
