5. Conclusions
The cooperation of the two courts of auditors has proven itself.
Thus, it was possible to obtain the necessary insights into the systems used in both countries. This applies in particular to: • Intra-Community sales, • Risk management in the VAT, in particular with regard to the selection of risky sales, • Recovery of VAT receivables and • VAT audit of large companies.
The audit revealed differences in the strategies for detecting VAT fraud and the systems discussed above.
These findings can be used to improve existing procedures.
They can also be used to initiate a discussion among interested parties on which audit approaches and anti-fraud strategies can be used. This applies z. Eg for the relationship within and between the Member States and the EU Commission.
The experience and insights gained should encourage us to continue jointly to examine the administration of VAT.
